v 3
d r3d: Regression Discontinuity with Distribution-valued Outcomes
d Program by David Van Dijcke, University of Michigan
d Distribution-Date: 28may2025
d
d This package implements regression discontinuity designs where the outcome
d is a distribution rather than a scalar. Supports both sharp and fuzzy RD,
d bootstrap inference, and optimal bandwidth selection.
d
d Author: David Van Dijcke
d Support: dvdijcke@umich.edu
d
d Required STATA version: 14.0
d
d KW: regression discontinuity
d KW: distributional outcomes
d KW: quantile treatment effects
d KW: causal inference
d
d Requires: STATA version 14.0
d
f ado/r3d.ado
f ado/r3d_bootstrap.ado
f ado/r3d_bwselect.ado
f ado/r3d_plugin_load.ado
f ado/r3d_setup.ado
f mata/r3d_mata.mata
f mata/r3d_plugin_interface.mata
f doc/r3d.sthlp
f doc/r3d_bootstrap.sthlp
f doc/r3d_bwselect.sthlp
f README.md
f INSTALL.md
f example.do
F ado/r3d_plugin.plugin
e
d
d The plugin file r3d_plugin.plugin provides enhanced performance
d but is optional. The package works with pure Mata if the plugin
d is not available or fails to load.
d
d After installation, Mata functions are automatically compiled
d when r3d is first run. No separate setup step is required.
d